BOLD START--><strong>Saturday Madness Raid</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is a weekly raid open to anyone level 50 or higher.<br>
<br>
Each week we choose a new object such as dragon slaying in WW, plane farming in Hate/Fear/Air/Growth, and armor farming in Kael.<br>
<br>
The raids start every Saturday at 2pm (Central Time Zone in America) and end at 2am (Central Time Zone in America).<br>
<br>
If a minimum of 40 people are not present by start time, the raid is called off for the week.<br>
<br>
<br>
*** Lewtz Rulez (Must Read And Agree To These Rules) ***<br>
All attending members are asigned a lewtz number for their class, and when an item drops that is useable by their class, the raid leader does a /rand for the total number of people in that class. If the /rand result is your asigned lewtz number for that class, you win the roll and pick up the item.<br>
<br>
Example: Your a cleric and you have been asigned lewtz number 4 for the cleric class out of 6 clerics that showed up. A cleric item drops off of a dragon, and the raid leader does a /rand 6. The result comes up as 4, and you get to lewt the item.<br>
<br>
If an item is useable by multiple classes, then the raid leader will do a /rand for each class that is capable of using the item, and then the individual winners of each of the classes does a /rand to see who gets to lewt the item.<br>
<br>
The point of this method of rolling on items is to minimize confusion while still remaining fair.<br>
<br>
All non-rollable lewtz will be sold to a NPC vendor and added to the pool of money gathered during the raid. This pool of money will be used to fund the raids each week paying for port gems, peridots, pearls, gate potions, etc.<br>
<br>
<br>
*** Raid Rulez (Must Read And Agree To These Rules) ***<br>
#1 Always listen to the raid leader at all times. The raid leader is doing the very best he or she can to make sure that you do not die, so pay attention and do your part as asked please.<br>
<br>
#2 Never kneel down on a monsters corpse. The raid leader is the only one who will ever kneel down on a monsters corpse <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>except</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the case of picking up non-drop items that you have won. Accidentally kneeling down on a dropped monster happens, but repeated actions will be taken as intentional, and you will be banned from future raids.<br>
<br>
#3 Ninja lewters will be perma banned. No exceptions!<br>
<br>
#4 Sign up on the Raid Signup System at www.JemandVerbieten.com ... The password to the raid system is 'bigem'.<br>
<br>
#5 Have fun.!<br>
